dismissalText.commentary: Angelo Mathews c †Sarfaraz Ahmed b Aizaz Cheema 3 (4b 0x4 0x6 7m) SR: 75

dismissalComment.html: huge appeal for caught behind and Pakistan review umpire Richard Illingworth's not-out decision. It was a short of a length delivery outside off stump, which Mathews tried to steer to third man. There was a definite noise as the ball passed the bat, although there was no obvious deviation. The noise is good enough for the umpires, though. The decision has been overturned and Mathews is on his way

dismissalText.commentary: Umar Akmal c Chandimal b Fernando 91 (102b 8x4 1x6 147m) SR: 89.21

dismissalComment.html: what has he done! After hitting three consecutive boundaries and bringing the asking-rate below six an over, Akmal's thrown it away. He made room once again by moving towards leg and hit a full ball hard and flat but straight to mid-on, where Chandimal took the catch. The ball was hit so hard that Chandimal fell backwards as he caught it and then tumbled over his head

headshotImage.caption: Dilhara Fernando player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Dilhara Fernando player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Shahid Afridi run out (Dilshan) 29 (14b 3x4 1x6 31m) SR: 207.14

dismissalComment.html: There's only one left now! Afridi's a goner. Ajmal played the ball close on the off side and Afridi began to thunder down the pitch for the single to get on strike. Dilshan was the fielder sprinting in from backward point, swooping on the ball with one hand, picking up cleanly and, in one fluid motion, throwing the ball under-arm to score a direct hit at the striker's end. Afridi was half a foot short and Dilshan is pumped

caught behind! Hafeez has nicked one that pitched on a good length around off and seamed away from the right-hander, he prodded at it from his crease without using his feet and got a thick edge, which Sangakkara caught with ease

stunning catch from Sangakkara! He leaped full length to his right to grab the ball with one hand from right in front of first slip. Younis had also poked at the away-seaming delivery without moving his feet and got an edge thicker than Hafeez's. Pakistan in early strife. Younis could have and should have let that go.

lbw! A low full toss that is dead straight and dipping on the batsman. Sarfraz tries to flick across the line and misses the ball. He's hit flush in front of the stumps. And just like that both set batsmen have been dismissed. On second thought, however, that might have been swinging down leg side. It looked close at normal speed though.

headshotImage.caption: Imran Farhat player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Imran Farhat player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: lbw! Farhat's been given but he's reviewed the decision. Did that pitch in line with the stumps? It did. The ball landed on middle from over the wicket and bent back into the left-hander, beating the bat as it came across the front pad to hit the knee roll. That is plumb. He was hit on the crease

headshotImage.caption: Umar Gul player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: this time he's been given! The ball was full and straight once again, Gul tried to play across the line and was hit on the pad plumb in front. Was there another inside edge though? I'll let you know soon. No inside edge. Out.

dismissalComment.html: it's all over! Ajmal backs away and slogs the ball in the air towards long-on, the batsmen run a single, but then decide to chance an overthrow after the ball passes the stumps at the bowler's end. Sangakkara is quick to anticipate this though, and is in position to collect the ball. He hits the stumps direct at the non-striker's end, running out Cheema

commentPreTextItems.html: Another ten runs and Sri Lanka might be concerned ...

commentTextItems.html: it's all over! Ajmal backs away and slogs the ball in the air towards long-on, the batsmen run a single, but then decide to chance an overthrow after the ball passes the stumps at the bowler's end. Sangakkara is quick to anticipate this though, and is in position to collect the ball. He hits the stumps direct at the non-striker's end, running out Cheema

commentPostTextItems.html: 10.55 pm The five-ODI series is now level 1-1. A quite fantastic performance in the field from Sri Lanka. Malinga gave them the early wickets that set back Pakistan right at the start. Umar Akmal threatened to win the game for Pakistan but he fell to a rush of blood to the head. Afridi attacked briefly but was then run out by a terrific piece of fielding, and that was the body blow to Pakistan's chase. Nitin Sundar's bulletin will be updated shortly.
Biju: "Ironical, but victory margin for Sri Lanka = number of extras conceded by Pakistan!"
The Man of the Match, announced after 2365 other awards for every aspect of the game, is Lasith Malinga.

Misbah-ul-Haq: "I think the way they started, taking three early wickets, we were under pressure. Everyone fought well until it end, it was a bad day for us. It was just a matter of playing 50 overs. I am happy with the way we fought after losing three early wickets. The youngsters really performed."

Tillakaratne Dilshan: "We needed this win. Everyone played very good cricket. I got a start but threw my wicket. We needed to get a start and we got that today. We planned for 240 but we were short about 20 runs. The bowlers did a great job, especially with the dew."
That's it from us at ESPNcricinfo today, thank you for all your emails. Good night.

dismissalText.commentary: Angelo Mathews c †Sarfaraz Ahmed b Aizaz Cheema 3 (4b 0x4 0x6 7m) SR: 75

dismissalComment.html: huge appeal for caught behind and Pakistan review umpire Richard Illingworth's not-out decision. It was a short of a length delivery outside off stump, which Mathews tried to steer to third man. There was a definite noise as the ball passed the bat, although there was no obvious deviation. The noise is good enough for the umpires, though. The decision has been overturned and Mathews is on his way

dismissalText.commentary: Mohammad Hafeez c †Sangakkara b Malinga 4 (3b 1x4 0x6 2m) SR: 133.33

dismissalComment.html: caught behind! Hafeez has nicked one that pitched on a good length around off and seamed away from the right-hander, he prodded at it from his crease without using his feet and got a thick edge, which Sangakkara caught with ease

dismissalText.commentary: Imran Farhat lbw b Perera 3 (10b 0x4 0x6 20m) SR: 30

dismissalComment.html: lbw! Farhat's been given but he's reviewed the decision. Did that pitch in line with the stumps? It did. The ball landed on middle from over the wicket and bent back into the left-hander, beating the bat as it came across the front pad to hit the knee roll. That is plumb. He was hit on the crease

dismissalText.commentary: Younis Khan c †Sangakkara b Malinga 0 (2b 0x4 0x6 2m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: stunning catch from Sangakkara! He leaped full length to his right to grab the ball with one hand from right in front of first slip. Younis had also poked at the away-seaming delivery without moving his feet and got an edge thicker than Hafeez's. Pakistan in early strife. Younis could have and should have let that go.

headshotImage.caption: Dilhara Fernando player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Dilhara Fernando player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Misbah-ul-Haq lbw b Fernando 21 (53b 0x4 0x6 90m) SR: 39.62

dismissalComment.html: lbw! No question about that one and I suspect Misbah knew it as soon as the ball slammed into his pad in front of middle stump. He moved across his crease to play on the leg side and was beaten by one that angled into him from a good length around off stump

headshotImage.caption: Dilhara Fernando player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Dilhara Fernando player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Dinesh Chandimal, player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Dinesh Chandimal, player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Umar Akmal c Chandimal b Fernando 91 (102b 8x4 1x6 147m) SR: 89.21

dismissalComment.html: what has he done! After hitting three consecutive boundaries and bringing the asking-rate below six an over, Akmal's thrown it away. He made room once again by moving towards leg and hit a full ball hard and flat but straight to mid-on, where Chandimal took the catch. The ball was hit so hard that Chandimal fell backwards as he caught it and then tumbled over his head

headshotImage.caption: Abdul Razzaq player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Abdul Razzaq player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Abdul Razzaq player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Abdul Razzaq player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Abdul Razzaq run out (Perera/Mendis) 11 (22b 0x4 0x6 19m) SR: 50

dismissalComment.html: Razzaq's been run out! Akmal hit the ball to wide long-on and the batsmen decided to run a difficult second. Perera's throw from the deep was flat and fast, reaching Mendis on the bounce. The bowler collected and broke the stumps with Razzaq about a foot short

dismissalText.commentary: Sarfaraz Ahmed lbw b Malinga 24 (37b 1x4 0x6 50m) SR: 64.86

dismissalComment.html: lbw! A low full toss that is dead straight and dipping on the batsman. Sarfraz tries to flick across the line and misses the ball. He's hit flush in front of the stumps. And just like that both set batsmen have been dismissed. On second thought, however, that might have been swinging down leg side. It looked close at normal speed though.

headshotImage.caption: Dilhara Fernando player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Dilhara Fernando player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Shahid Afridi run out (Dilshan) 29 (14b 3x4 1x6 31m) SR: 207.14

dismissalComment.html: There's only one left now! Afridi's a goner. Ajmal played the ball close on the off side and Afridi began to thunder down the pitch for the single to get on strike. Dilshan was the fielder sprinting in from backward point, swooping on the ball with one hand, picking up cleanly and, in one fluid motion, throwing the ball under-arm to score a direct hit at the striker's end. Afridi was half a foot short and Dilshan is pumped
